---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair across SoCal, RS/RF column, ActiveSmart, integrated French Door. NZ premium (Haier). $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/fisher-paykel-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Fisher & Paykel still a New Zealand company or is it Chinese now?",
    a: "Both answers are true in different senses. Fisher & Paykel was founded in Auckland in 1934 by Woolf Fisher and Maurice Paykel, and the engineering, design, and product development teams are still based in East Tāmaki, Auckland today. Since 2012 the parent company has been Haier Group, the Qingdao-based Chinese conglomerate that also owns GE Appliances (in the US) and Haier the namesake brand. Practically, what that means for repair in LA: the Fisher & Paykel DNA on the product side, the ActiveSmart sensor platform, CoolDrawer design language, DishDrawer architecture, is still NZ-engineered. Parts chain has strengthened considerably since the Haier acquisition because Haier's GE Appliances infrastructure handles North American logistics for Fisher & Paykel service parts. 3–5 business days to LA on factory-exact items is the typical lead time our guys quote now; pre-2015 it was longer."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Fisher & Paykel and DCS, our techs keep hearing the names together?",
    a: "Correct, and it matters for service scope. DCS, Dynamic Cooking Systems, is a commercial-kitchen-derived outdoor grill and indoor pro-range brand based in Huntington Beach, CA. Fisher & Paykel acquired DCS in 2004, which is why the two brands show up together on the same authorized-dealer lists in LA. Under Haier's 2012 acquisition of F&P, DCS came along as a sibling brand. The scope split is clear: DCS does outdoor grills, outdoor-rated fridges, indoor pro-style ranges, and outdoor-kitchen ventilation. Fisher & Paykel does indoor residential refrigeration, dishwashers (DishDrawer), laundry, and a small indoor cooking range. We service both; this page covers Fisher & Paykel refrigerators only. DCS outdoor refrigeration lives on a separate combo slot (the /brands/dcs/ hub is pending launch). When a Pacific Palisades or Malibu household has both a DCS grill outside and an F&P fridge inside, we run the service visit combined."
  },
  {
    q: "Our kitchen designer specified an Integrated French Door from Fisher & Paykel, does it need special service attention compared to a freestanding unit?",
    a: "Yes. The Integrated French Door is F&P's panel-ready column-class fridge designed to disappear into the cabinetry, the door fronts accept custom cabinet panels, the top is flush with upper cabinetry, and the plinth kick sits in line with the adjacent runs. Service-side implications are real. First: any door-related repair (gasket, hinge, door-switch) requires removing the cabinet panel carefully, preserving the hinge offset, and reinstalling with a shim check against the original flush plane. Our techs photograph the reveal gap with tape markers before pulling hardware. Second: the Integrated French Door uses a narrower depth than a standard freestanding 36-inch F&P, so the refrigeration architecture is packed tighter, condenser access is different, fan service has less clearance, and the evaporator drain routing on certain RF series sometimes runs behind the pantry box. Third: panel weight. Custom hardwood or veneered panels add 15–35 pounds to the door versus stainless, hinge wear accelerates if the installer didn't adjust the closer tension for panel load. We check closer tension on every Integrated French Door service call."
  },
  {
    q: "What is ActiveSmart and what does it mean when the fridge temperature reads wrong?",
    a: "ActiveSmart is Fisher & Paykel's variable-speed compressor and multi-sensor cooling platform. Older residential fridges run a single-speed compressor that cycles on and off to hold a setpoint; ActiveSmart runs a variable-speed compressor that modulates up and down with demand, controlled by multiple temperature and humidity sensors reading each compartment and zone separately. In service terms it's genuinely better at holding temperature under load (groceries just put away, door opened a lot on a party night), and it runs quieter at steady-state. Failure modes are different from single-speed architectures though. A faulty sensor on ActiveSmart can mislead the compressor into running too slow or too fast, symptom looks like \"warm fridge\" or \"fridge too cold\" without the compressor sounding wrong. Diagnosis on ActiveSmart platforms starts at the sensor tree, not the compressor. We carry the F&P diagnostic interface cable on the truck to read the sensor state directly rather than guess."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service the CoolDrawer, the stand-alone drawer refrigerator?",
    a: "Yes. The CoolDrawer (RB series) is a unique F&P product, a single-drawer refrigerator that converts between five modes (fresh food, chill, pantry, freezer, wine) through the ActiveSmart control. It installs under a counter or in a kitchen island, and it's spec'd a lot in LA entertaining kitchens where the main fridge is elsewhere and the island needs a beverage or produce zone within arm's reach. Common service: drawer slide rail wear (heavy drawer + daily use + tall loads), gasket replacement on the drawer perimeter, and ActiveSmart control-board service. The five-mode conversion is a firmware-driven feature, if the drawer won't switch modes or locks into one mode, it's usually a control issue, not the refrigeration cycle. Firmware updates resolve a portion of those calls; control-board replacement handles the rest. CoolDrawer gaskets are a proprietary profile, we order from the F&P parts channel, typical 3–5 day lead time to LA."
  },
  {
    q: "Our 10-year-old RF540ADUX ice-maker stopped making ice, is that expected and what does repair cost?",
    a: "10 years is about the edge of \"expected\" on an F&P ice-maker without descaling maintenance, especially in LA's harder-water neighborhoods (Encino, Sherman Oaks, Calabasas, Tarzana, Pasadena, mineral content runs higher than the coastal Westside). The common failure chain on F&P French Door ice-makers: fill valve scales up, water flow drops, ice-mold fills partially, ejector motor strains, and eventually the module stops cycling. Our diagnostic order: check fill pressure at the valve, descale the water path, verify the valve solenoid is still opening fully, then inspect the ejector module and ice-mold thermistor. Standard service with descaling and fill-valve inspection runs $280–$440; fill-valve replacement if it's scaled beyond service lands $320–$520 including labor; full ice-maker module swap on an RF540 is $480–$760 depending on whether it's the original module or a revised SKU. If a household is running heavy ice production on hard-water supply, we recommend annual descaling going forward. RF540 specifically had a revised ice-maker module on units built after mid-2018; if your unit is earlier we factor that into the quote."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your typical pricing for Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common F&P refrigerator bands our techs quote: door gasket replacement $220–$400 on freestanding, $280–$460 on Integrated French Door (panel weight + shim adds labor); ActiveSmart temperature sensor $180–$340; condenser fan motor $280–$480; evaporator fan $260–$440; defrost heater and thermostat $300–$520; ActiveSmart control board $520–$820; CoolDrawer slide rail replacement $260–$440; Integrated French Door hinge re-shim and alignment $240–$420; ice-maker service or module swap $280–$780 depending on the fault; variable-speed compressor replacement (RS column, RF French Door) $1,100–$2,000 depending on refrigerant and size. For units 12-plus years old with compressor-side faults we walk through the repair-vs-replace math with current replacement cost on your specific SKU before quoting the compressor job."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair covered under a 90-day warranty on parts and labor?",
    a: "Our labor warranty is 90 days on the specific fault we repaired. Factory parts we install carry the Fisher & Paykel parts warranty, which is typically 90 days on small parts and one year on major components (compressor, evaporator, sealed-system items) under the F&P aftermarket channel. If the exact fault we fixed recurs within 90 days, we come back at no charge for labor; parts are covered by the F&P parts warranty whichever is longer. If a different fault surfaces, a new failure in a different subsystem, that's a separate service call. We document the scope of each repair in writing on the invoice so the warranty boundary is clear. Our techs prefer this level of documentation because F&P's multi-sensor architecture means follow-up faults are occasionally real and the original-repair warranty shouldn't be tangled with them."
  },
  {
    q: "Are your technicians Fisher & Paykel factory-certified specifically?",
    a: "We service Fisher & Paykel as a regular part of our luxury and premium brand scope. Factory-certified programs for F&P in the US are coordinated through the authorized dealer network and a handful of independent service companies that carry factory-certification for first-year warranty coverage. Our techs are trained on the F&P platforms (ActiveSmart, Integrated French Door, CoolDrawer, DishDrawer) and we run the F&P diagnostic interface on service calls. For units still under factory warranty, call the dealer that sold the appliance or Fisher & Paykel customer care to route to the factory-authorized service network. For units out of warranty, our team handles the service directly and we source genuine F&P parts through the aftermarket channel."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service older Fisher & Paykel refrigerators from before the Haier acquisition?",
    a: "Yes, and that's a meaningful chunk of our F&P service calls, the 2005–2012 Auckland-built units are still in plenty of LA kitchens. Pre-Haier F&P refrigerators used the earlier ActiveSmart platform (different sensor architecture, different control board) and the earlier RF and E series lineups. Parts availability on those older platforms is the main service question: the F&P aftermarket channel still ships most service-critical parts for 2005-onwards units, but specific boards and some sensor modules for pre-2010 units occasionally require sourcing from secondary suppliers. Our techs have parts relationships for the older platforms. If a 15-plus-year-old F&P fridge has a fault that would need a discontinued control board, we'll tell you straight whether repair pencils vs. replacing the unit, that honest call matters more at that age than trying to force a repair that costs more than a new fridge."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official Fisher & Paykel manual or warranty information?",
      a: `Our technicians work independently of Fisher & Paykel's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair across Los Angeles, RS column series, RF French Door freestanding, Integrated French Door panel-ready, CoolDrawer single-drawer, ActiveSmart variable-speed platform, ice-maker service. New Zealand-designed, Haier-owned. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Fisher & Paykel", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/fisher-paykel/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Fisher & Paykel fridge acting up? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Fisher & Paykel › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>Fisher & Paykel Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Fisher & Paykel is the New Zealand-born refrigeration specialist that architects spec into modernist LA
            kitchens when the brief is "integrated, quiet, thoughtful." Our techs service the full US Fisher & Paykel
            refrigeration lineup, RS series column built-ins, RF series French Door freestanding, Integrated French
            Door panel-ready, CoolDrawer single-drawer units, and ActiveSmart ice-makers, across Silver Lake,
            Hollywood Hills, Pacific Palisades, Beverly Hills, and the Westside. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential
            diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>ActiveSmart platform depth</b>, variable-speed compressor + multi-sensor tree diagnosed properly</li>
            <li><b>Integrated French Door specialty</b>, panel-ready shim protocol, hinge offset preserved</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
            <li><b>Auckland-designed since 1934</b>, Haier-owned parent since 2012, parts chain strong</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Fisher & Paykel in LA, who owns one and what our techs see</h2>
      <p>
        Fisher & Paykel refrigeration in LA is a specifier's choice. Most households that own an F&P fridge didn't
        walk into a big-box retailer and pick it off the floor, they bought it on a kitchen designer's or architect's
        recommendation, usually because the kitchen was being built in a modernist idiom (flat-panel cabinetry,
        integrated appliances, European or Japanese design sensibility) and Fisher & Paykel's Integrated French Door
        or RS column platform fit the spec. We service F&P refrigerators regularly in Silver Lake, Echo Park, and the
        Hollywood Hills hillside-modern houses, mid-century Case Study or Eichler-descendant homes where the kitchen
        is a single continuous cabinetry line and a Sub-Zero column would be the default choice but the owner wanted
        something with F&P's lighter-weight visual presence.
      </p>
      <p>
        The other F&P household we see regularly in LA is the pro-style outdoor-kitchen owner in Pacific Palisades,
        Malibu, and Newport Coast, where the outdoor space has a DCS grill (Fisher & Paykel's sibling brand under
        the same Haier ownership) and the kitchen inside runs a matching F&P package. Brand-family consistency is a
        real factor for that clientele. Our guys service F&P and DCS on the same visit when both are installed;
        parts for both route through the Haier-integrated North American channel, which since 2012 has meaningfully
        shortened the service timeline compared to the pre-Haier era.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Fisher & Paykel refrigerator failures our techs see most often</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from running F&P service across LA. Six clusters cover most of the dispatch. ActiveSmart's
        multi-sensor architecture means diagnosis order matters, a symptom that looks like a compressor fault is
        often a sensor fault, and the fix is smaller than the symptom suggests.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>ActiveSmart sensor drift, fridge reads wrong without the compressor sounding wrong</h3>
        <p>
          Most-common call. Compartment temperature drifts warm or cold, but the compressor sounds normal and the
          door seal is intact. On ActiveSmart platforms a variable-speed compressor modulates based on what the
          sensors tell it; a drifted sensor tells the compressor to run too slow or too fast, and the compartment
          misses setpoint. Our diagnostic order on ActiveSmart: read sensor state through the F&P diagnostic
          interface, verify each zone's sensor against a calibrated probe, and replace the drifted sensor. Sensor
          replacement is a small job; misdiagnosing it as a compressor problem is the expensive mistake. Typical
          sensor service $180–$340.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Integrated French Door panel drift, reveal gap opens after a year or two</h3>
        <p>
          Panel-ready Integrated French Door units installed with heavy hardwood or veneered cabinet panels: after
          12–24 months the panel drops slightly on one side, the reveal gap widens, and the homeowner notices the
          once-flush plane has moved. Cause is usually the door closer tension wasn't increased to match the panel
          weight at commissioning, and the hinge has settled. Fix is hinge re-shim plus closer tension adjustment;
          we carry the F&P offset gauge and the closer-spring kit on the truck. 90 minutes for the service call.
          Occasionally the root cause is cabinet settling (scope for a cabinet contractor, not us), we tell you
          which side of the issue is ours.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Condenser fan motor noise, variable-speed compressor sounds fine, the fan doesn't</h3>
        <p>
          On ActiveSmart architectures the variable-speed compressor runs remarkably quiet at steady-state, which
          makes condenser fan noise stand out. Fan bearing wear on RS column fridges shows up around year 7–9 as a
          low-frequency hum or intermittent rattle that the homeowner sometimes attributes to the compressor. Meter
          the fan motor amperage, verify the bearing play by hand, replace from truck stock. $280–$480 typical.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Evaporator drain ice-up on RF French Door, water pooling in the bottom drawer</h3>
        <p>
          RF series French Door fridges have a drain routing from the evaporator that occasionally freezes over if
          the defrost heater cycle isn't completing correctly, or if debris has migrated into the drain opening.
          Symptom: water pooling in the bottom drawer, a small puddle under the fridge, or periodic ice sheets
          forming on the freezer floor. Fix is defrost + drain-clear + verifying the defrost heater and thermostat
          are cycling on schedule. If the heater element is weak we replace it; if the thermostat is stuck the
          replacement is 60 minutes. Drain-only service without heater/thermostat work is a 45-minute job.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>CoolDrawer won't switch modes, firmware or control-board, usually not refrigeration</h3>
        <p>
          CoolDrawer (RB series) standalone drawer fridges convert between five modes under firmware control. When
          the drawer refuses to switch modes or locks into a single mode, 8 out of 10 times it's firmware, we run
          the service update, clear the fault, and the drawer works. The other 2 times it's a control-board fault
          and we swap the board. Refrigeration cycle itself is usually fine when this symptom shows up. Firmware
          update $120–$180; control-board replacement $480–$720.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker mineral buildup, LA hard-water pattern on RF and Integrated French Door</h3>
        <p>
          Ice production drops progressively over 6–12 months on households in Encino, Sherman Oaks, Tarzana,
          Calabasas, Pasadena, LA's harder-water areas. Fill valve scales, flow drops, ice-mold only partially
          fills, ejector strains. Descaling plus fill-valve inspection resolves most cases. If the valve has scaled
          past service it gets replaced. On units installed pre-2018 we also check the ice-maker module revision
         , F&P revised the ice-maker assembly on several RF SKUs mid-2018 and the newer module runs more
          reliably in hard-water conditions. Annual descaling recommended for heavy-ice households going forward.
          Descale + valve $280–$440.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Fisher & Paykel US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        The US F&P residential refrigerator lineup is built around four platforms. European SKUs that don't ship to
        the US aren't included, our scope below reflects what's actually sold and installed in LA kitchens.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>RS series, 24" / 36" / 48" column built-ins</h3>
          <p>F&P's luxury column platform. RS36A72J and RS90A1 are the common LA installs. ActiveSmart variable-speed
          platform, panel-ready or stainless finish, column-pair or solo installs. Direct competitor to Sub-Zero
          columns and Liebherr Monolith. Service-accessible condenser in the lower rear enclosure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>RF series, French Door freestanding</h3>
          <p>Counter-depth and full-depth French Door fridges. RF540ADUX, RF610ADUBX, RF522ADUBX are common in LA
          kitchens, 36" and 30" widths, bottom freezer drawer, ice-maker on select SKUs. ActiveSmart platform;
          Variable Temperature Zone drawer on upper-tier SKUs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Integrated French Door, panel-ready 36" built-in</h3>
          <p>The signature modernist-kitchen SKU. Panel-ready doors accept custom cabinet panels, the top sits flush
          with upper cabinetry, refrigerator-freezer column architecture in a French Door layout. Installed in
          Case Study-style homes, Silver Lake modern hillsides, and Hollywood Hills architect renovations. Requires
          panel-weight-adjusted hinge closer tension at commissioning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>CoolDrawer, single-drawer convertible refrigerator</h3>
          <p>RB36 and RB24 series. Standalone drawer fridge that converts between fresh food, chill, pantry, freezer,
          and wine modes under ActiveSmart control. Installs under kitchen island counters or in secondary
          entertaining zones. Heavy slide-rail wear on high-use installations; proprietary perimeter gasket profile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Variable Temperature Zone (VTZ) drawer</h3>
          <p>Integrated convertible zone on upper-tier RF French Door SKUs, the drawer switches between freezer,
          soft-freeze, and fresh-food modes. Common service: sensor drift within the zone (ActiveSmart reads each
          zone separately), gasket on the drawer perimeter, and defrost cycle on freezer-mode service calls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>IR24X / IR30X under-counter and built-in refrigerators</h3>
          <p>Integrated compact built-ins, 24" and 30" widths. Installed in butler's pantries, wet bars, and
          secondary kitchens. Single-zone refrigeration, panel-ready fronts, simpler service profile than the RS
          column platform. Parts chain runs through the same F&P aftermarket route as the larger platforms.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Fisher & Paykel vs Sub-Zero vs Liebherr, how our techs think about the column landscape</h2>
      <p>
        Three brands dominate LA architect-spec column refrigeration above the $8K price point: Sub-Zero, Liebherr,
        and Fisher & Paykel. Miele MasterCool is a fourth in the mix on the highest end. Customers sometimes ask our
        techs which to pick before they buy; we don't sell appliances so we have no commercial stake in the answer,
        but after a decade servicing all of them the pattern is worth stating straight.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Sub-Zero</b> is the US luxury default, Wisconsin-built, family-owned (Bakke family since 1945), strongest
        parts supply chain in LA (same-day or next-day to Bel Air and Beverly Hills). See
        <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Liebherr</b> is the European modernist alternative, family-owned Austrian-German, BioFresh adjustable-humidity
        drawers, tight integrated-install tolerances. Parts 3–5 days to LA. See
        <a href="/brands/liebherr-refrigerator-repair/">Liebherr refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Fisher & Paykel</b> is the Auckland-designed, Haier-backed alternative, ActiveSmart variable-speed platform,
        Integrated French Door as the signature panel-ready SKU, generally lighter visual presence and quieter at
        steady-state than the heavier-industrial competition. Parts 3–5 days to LA through the Haier-integrated North
        American channel. Often picked when the kitchen is modernist rather than traditional-luxury, or when the
        household already runs F&P DishDrawer dishwashers and wants brand-family consistency.
      </p>
      <p>
        None of the four is objectively "better." Sub-Zero wins on parts availability and US-brand familiarity,
        Liebherr wins on integrated tolerances and column depth options, Miele wins on engineering-life reputation,
        Fisher & Paykel wins on modernist aesthetic and quieter variable-speed behavior. Our team services all four
        equally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What Fisher & Paykel refrigerator repair typically costs</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts and labor vary with platform generation (pre-Haier 2005–2012 vs. current), specific SKU,
      and whether the fault is on the refrigeration, door, or control side.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (freestanding RF)</td><td>$220 – $400</td><td>Standard French Door or column profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (Integrated French Door)</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>Panel-weight-adjusted shim + closer re-tension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ActiveSmart temperature sensor</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Diagnosed via F&P service interface</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$280 – $480</td><td>Common RS and RF amperage specs on truck</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan / defrost heater</td><td>$260 – $520</td><td>RF drain ice-up or temperature-drift cases</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ActiveSmart firmware update</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Resolves most CoolDrawer mode-switch faults</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Integrated French Door hinge re-shim</td><td>$240 – $420</td><td>F&P offset gauge required</td></tr>
